<br>
Lineup...<br>
<br>
I would use <br>
<br>
ToT<br>
Swap (slow default if no shaman, but shaman definately preferred)<br>
Root (immobilize or mabye even paralyzing earth)<br>
Glamor of Kintaz<br>
Flux<br>
Slant<br>
Tash<br>
Dazzle<br>
<br>
Thats what i would use off the top of my head.  If i have a shaman ( preferrable ), i would put charm (boltrans) in swap.<br>
<br>
I dont think too many of the shrooms are 56+ (adepts and reavers ? you shroom experts let us know ), so you dont have to use GoK on all the shroom, only the 56+ ones.<br>
<br>
If you have anyone down there that is level 56, get them to /con all incomming mobs and say level as soon as they can (if its even to them, you will need GoK on that particular mob).<br>
<br>
I would tash the shrooms, as i hear they have decent MR and tash will help you land spells on them, and you need to stun the healing ones to keep them from healing themselves ( thus slant, for the larger range and still relatively fast casting time, over shift , whose area is too small, or skew, whose casting time is too slow )<br>
<br>
I hear the king is almost impossible to land a slow spell on .. mabye a 60 shaman with malo + tash can do it easier ?  I guess you just tank him down, and try to prevent any other shrooms from healing him by mezzing them.<br>
<br>
I know Root is good Crowd Control down here, and root parking non healing shrooms works pretty well.  If they are slowed, and parked, they dont need to be mezzed and can save you a lot of mana.<br>
<br>
The only reason i havent gone to shrooms, is because its not that good exp, and i would like a cloak for arodan.  If i go, i either want to go in a group of my friends so that i know i wont get screwed on &quot;NEED&quot; on the tunic, or,  would allow me to roll on one if they didnt &quot;need&quot; it ( ie shaman, or monk).<br>
<br>
