<br>
Learn to hate GoK! I do <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Rapture is so so so so so much nicer. /hug rapture <p><br><br>
Gnome extraordinaire <a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=4830">Noggel Nimbelnoggin</a><br>
Pansy Ranger <a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=20396">Lythelas Manasponge</a><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uerrtai.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Errtai</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Cyber Pimp</span><br> <font color=#000033>(7/5/01 10:57:28 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Enchanters and Shrooms</span><hr size=1> Shhh.. Istrahd, don't listen to the nay-sayers.<br>
<br>
I have spent untold hours at the shroom camp, starting at level 56.  Level 56 was pretty low... back then I would have a higher (level 59) shaman and a level 60 tank to pull to even things out.  Nowadays though, I can go down there with no shaman and lower level tanks and still pull the king spawn.<br>
<br>
It's true about Glamour of Kintaz - that spell sucks.  It's like a &quot;necessary evil&quot; spell, I guess it's better than not being able to mez at all.<br>
<br>
Remember, the myconid warriors and myconid preists are both always Dazzle-able.  The myconid adepts and myconid reavers may POSSIBLY need GOK.  I've found that only 1 out of every 4 or 5 reavers or adepts need GOK.  If you are of the appropriate level you could just con them and see, but I don't have a problem any more with firing off Dazzle once, seeing the &quot;can't be mezzed by this spell&quot; message, then firing off GOK.<br>
<br>
At 57 you're going to get beat down pretty badly and have some resists.  One school of thought says just tash first, take the beating and try to channel out mez.  This strategy doesn't sit well with me though and even in my earlier days I tried dazzle first.  Some enchanters go by either stategy though.  At 60 I *never* have to tash first.  I'll Dazzle, if resisted I tash while Dazzle is refreshing then try again.<br>
<br>
Take a level 57+ shaman down there with you the first couple of times until you get the hang of things.  Just swap out your usual druid evacer for him because you can just zone out down there.  After a few trips and another level, you may not even need the shaman any more and you could Forlorn Deeds everything also.  I have no trouble keeping up with mana down there for slows, GOKs, whatever. (I guess epic helps)<br>
<br>
Memming root might be a good idea, simply because you're going to have a much easier time channeling it out at your level (or any level for that matter) than a GOK.  When I do one group juggers I use Fetter basically as a swap out for GOK.  Since 1 group takes a bit of time to kill a Jugger, you don't want to stand there and use GOK 6 or 7 times on him to keep him mezzed.  Better to just Fetter, tash, slow.<br>
<br>
I think I got off on several different tangents... let me know how you do down there <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Oh one last thing, make sure you figure out BEFOREHAND how you will roll on any fungal regen tunics that drop.  I have seen more arguments over this item then maybe any other.  Whenever *I'm* in a group, I say simply that the tunic will be an item all 6 people in the group roll on no matter what.  Since the Shroom camp is slightly more exciting to me then a Karnor moat group, and I am level 60, there's really no other reason for me to be down there.  Whenever anyone has disagreed, I said okay cool, go ahead and grab another enchanter.  That always shuts em up :P<br>
<br>
