 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukelarnivmistweb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kelarniv Mistweb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(7/5/01 11:13:10 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Enchanters and Shrooms</span><hr size=1> Damn you people, making fun of my pet spell GoK! It's 275 mana for a whole 30 seconds! :P. <br>
<br>
That aside, at 57 shrooms will be tough to do without a shaman. You'll probably need to tash everything for a mez to hit, and somone else slowing will make a world of difference. Make sure you DON'T camp someplace near a major shroom highway (Pretty much anywhere near king)- though 7 add fights are lots of fun, you won't be able to handle them at 57 and even at 60 luck runs out sometime. <br>
<br>
Keep one thing in mind: About half of adepts are 55+, and though you can dazzle most of them, the 55+ ones will not be stunnable, even though you get the message. And Adepts don't do anything but try and get off CHs once they hit 50%, so mez interrupts are very effective against them. You really don't need an Adept CHing 4 times while you're holding down two shrooms, one of them requiring GoK (I've had this happen, ugh). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uqueldarya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Queldarya</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(7/5/01 11:17:23 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Enchanters and Shrooms</span><hr size=1> (Edited to poke fun at Errtai)<br>
<br>
Errtai - You still pull the King to the zone out room?  That's so...newbish. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Rawr-Enchanters (and those who simply die a lot like me) camp behind the King podium.<br>
<br>
/boggle noggel (hey, that rhymes <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   )<br>
<br>
Rapture is a VILE spell.  Any spell where that competes with ToT for recast time is VILE.  (Okie, maybe I'm exaggering that recast time a bit, but it's still vile.)<br>
<br>
Shrooms.  I end up in shrooms a lot for some reason.  I usually load:<br>
Dazzle<br>
Tash<br>
Memblur<br>
Two AE stuns<br>
GoK<br>
Either a dispel or a slow spell<br>
<br>
*  I'm not 100% sure what spells shrooms buff themselves with, but it seems that I get less resists after I hit them with a dispell, so I think there's cleric mobs which cast a RM spell of some sort (Adepts, Priests).  While I'm not a 100% certain, I think there's shaman types who also haste shrooms.  Try mez'ing first, if you get a resist, try dispelling.<br>
<br>
*  Shrooms hit hard and fast, and the higher level ones have long memories like Ilis and Reet frogs, so it's always nice to have a memblur so you can sit down and med during multiple add situations (and to have the shrooms leave the cleric alone).<br>
<br>
*  I occasionally load a slow, but usually 55+ shaman you didn't even know existed will come boiling out of the woodwork if they hear the phrase &quot;shroom camp&quot;, so having a shaman usually isn't a big problem.<br>
<br>
* It's difficult, almost impossible, to land most spells on the King (including slow).  I usually dispell it, wait a bit, then tash it, and let the shaman try and land a slow.  I believe the King is also a melee-range casting mob, so get close if you're going to try slowing it.  I simply concentrate on CC'ing any adds (and charm tanking, if you're comfortable with charming mobs, I usually don't have the mana to spare).  If your party isn't familiar with the King camp, explain this to them, so the cleric will know to be near FM.<br>
<br>
- As a side note, there's a neat way to effectively single pull the King.  Since the King has a larger aggro radius than the other shrooms he shares his little podium with, you can aggro one of the lower-level wanderers who pass &quot;behind&quot; the King, and that will get you two shrooms instead of three higher level ones at once.<br>
<br>
