<br>
GoK- I have used this as crowd control once during this time.  You will almost never have 2_ 56 mobs in the camp at once, just call a switch.  I do use it to interrupt complete heal.<br>
<br>
tactics- I am a huge_ advocate of bringing a krup with you to this camp, a dual wielding hasted krup and you dont even need to slow really if youre lom and you will basicly make like 90% of the xp you would at an xp camp.  We typically plow 20+ shrooms a cycle with krup and ragebringer rogue in group, most will die in under a minute.  The reason you dont have to slow is the krup will tank 80% of the time with the new pet aggros, and with his ~10k hps will need less healing than you would on a regular warrior with_ slow.  Usually needs a cheal once every 2-3 shrooms.  Now when this will suck is when you are dealing with shroom mez resists (which will happen fairly often) and the charm breaks, but if you have a group that is heads up about the charm and helps you out it will usually be ok.  To tell the truth I dont even use slow at this camp I would rather have a mana reserve for controlling the krup.<br>
<br>
    You will see alot of chealers wander by, these piss me off I will usually just tash them in and mez them if I see them, would rather have it in the camp than stealth healing.<br>
<br>
root- I keep this up always and use it on basicly everything, the mana you gain form being able to med right away is &gt; the cost of the spell, and it not running around beating healers is nice too.<br>
<br>
tash- tash everything, enspecially if not all of your stunners are high level, 56 and lower will have a hard time stunning if it isnt tashed, even I have trouble at 59 on about 1/3 of them without tash.<br>
<br>
I dont know what else to say, basicly shissared krup will out taunt any real player in your group and is &gt; than even shroom king with heals, play your group as a charm vehicle and you wont have much trouble.<br>
